// %  Difference between Cellpadding and Cellspacing
// %  Cellpadding:Cellpadding specifies the space between the border of a table cell and its contents (i.e)
// %   it defines the whitespace between the cell edge and the content of the cell.(ander)

// %  Syntax:
// %  <table cellpadding="value" >.....</table>
// %  where, value determines the padding 
// %  (space between the border of a table and its content)
// %  Cellspacing:Cellspacing specifies the space between cells (i.e) it defines the whitespace between the edges of the adjacent cells.(bahir)

// %  Syntax:
// %  <table cellspacing="value" >.....</table>
// %  where, value determines the padding 
// %  (space between adjacent cells) 
 




// %        important to note that :- 
// %          width="50" height="100"  yeh thead ko affect nhi kary ga means no chang
        
// %         row and colspan difference 
// %           ROWSPAN is used to combine the cells vertically. It merges the number of cells vertically and 
// %           displays them as a single cell. COLSPAN is used to combine the cells horizontally. 
// %          It specifies the number of columns that the cells span across and shows them as a single cell. 



// %                                  form
// % An HTML form is a section of a document containing normal content, markup, special elements called controls
// % (checkboxes, radio buttons, menus, etc.), and labels on those controls.

